Pronunciation:
Notes:
Citations
Date:  21/1/1929
Source:  NZ Journal of Agriculture
Author:
Vol / Page:  61
Edition:
Quote:  Another highly perfumed native plant growing there [New Plymouth] was the koheriki (aniseed - Angelica rosaefolia) highly appreciated by shepherds as well as their flocks. in fact, shepherds are so fond of it that it is becoming scarce in a wild state, and shepherds often dry the leaves and rub them up in their tobacco to give it an aroma. Koheriki is a little plant 1ft to 2 ft in height that is very suitable on rock-work in the open.
